"title": "5113: Peter, the disciple",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5113: peter, the disciple",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The son of Jonas or John, he was called Simon until Jesus Christ gave him the name Peter meaning “rock”.</p>\n<h2>Peter's background and family</h2>\n<h3>He lived in Capernaum</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:14\">MAT 8:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:29\">MRK 1:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:38\">LUK 4:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:44\">JHN 1:44</a> <em>He originally came from Bethsaida.</em></p>\n<h3>He was a fisherman by trade</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:10\">LUK 5:10</a></p>\n<h2>Peter as Jesus Christ's disciple</h2>\n<h3>He was called by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:18-Matt4:20\">MAT 4:18–4:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:16-Mark1:20\">MRK 1:16–1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:10\">LUK 5:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:40-John1:42\">JHN 1:40–1:42</a></p>\n<h3>He witnessed Jesus Christ perform many miracles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:14-Matt8:15\">MAT 8:14–8:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:30-Mark1:31\">MRK 1:30–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:38-Luke4:39\">LUK 4:38–4:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24-Matt17:27\">MAT 17:24–17:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:4-Luke5:8\">LUK 5:4–5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:2-John21:6\">JHN 21:2–21:6</a></p>\n<h3>He was chosen to be with Jesus Christ on certain occasions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:1-Matt17:2\">MAT 17:1–17:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2\">MRK 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:28-Luke9:29\">LUK 9:28–9:29</a> <em>at the transfiguration of Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:36-Matt26:37\">MAT 26:36–26:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:32-Mark14:33\">MRK 14:32–14:33</a> <em>in the Garden of Gethsemane</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:37\">MRK 5:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:51\">LUK 8:51</a></p>\n<h3>He sometimes acted as spokesman for the other disciples</h3>\n<p>He asked Jesus Christ to teach them:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:15\">MAT 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21\">MAT 18:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:15-Matt16:16\">MAT 16:15–16:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:29\">MRK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:20\">LUK 9:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:69\">JHN 6:69</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:4\">MAT 17:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:5\">MRK 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:33\">LUK 9:33</a> <em>He asked Jesus Christ to prolong the transfiguration experience</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:27\">MAT 19:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:28\">MRK 10:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:28\">LUK 18:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:36-Mark1:37\">MRK 1:36–1:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:4-Luke5:5\">LUK 5:4–5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:68\">JHN 6:68</a></p>\n<h3>His impetuous nature interacted with his devotion to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:28-Matt14:29\">MAT 14:28–14:29</a> <em>He wanted to walk to Jesus Christ on the water</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:22\">MAT 16:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:32\">MRK 8:32</a> <em>He tried to prevent Jesus Christ from going to his death</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:35\">MAT 26:35</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:31\">MRK 14:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:33\">LUK 22:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:37\">JHN 13:37</a> <em>He vowed that he was willing to die for Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:6-John13:8\">JHN 13:6–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:10\">JHN 18:10</a></p>\n<h3>He was the subject of both special commendation and rebuke</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:17-Matt16:19\">MAT 16:17–16:19</a> <em>He was commended for his confession of faith in Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:23\">MAT 16:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:33\">MRK 8:33</a> <em>He was rebuked for his opposition to Jesus Christ's prediction of his suffering</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:34\">MAT 26:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:30\">MRK 14:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:34\">LUK 22:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:38\">JHN 13:38</a> <em>He was warned that he would disown Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:40-Matt26:41\">MAT 26:40–26:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:37-Mark14:38\">MRK 14:37–14:38</a> <em>He was rebuked for falling asleep in the Garden of Gethsemane</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:10-John18:11\">JHN 18:10–18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:20-John21:22\">JHN 21:20–21:22</a></p>\n<h2>Peter's denial of Jesus Christ and his reinstatement</h2>\n<h3>He denied that he knew Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:69-Matt26:74\">MAT 26:69–26:74</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:66-Mark14:71\">MRK 14:66–14:71</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:54-Luke22:60\">LUK 22:54–22:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:15-John18:18\">JHN 18:15–18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:25-John18:27\">JHN 18:25–18:27</a></p>\n<h3>He repented of his denial</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:75\">MAT 26:75</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:72\">MRK 14:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:61-Luke22:62\">LUK 22:61–22:62</a></p>\n<h3>The risen Christ appeared to him on his own</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:33-Luke24:34\">LUK 24:33–24:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:4-1Cor15:5\">1CO 15:4–15:5</a></p>\n<h3>He was reinstated by Jesus Christ in front of other disciples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:17\">JHN 21:15–21:17</a></p>",
